JSDoc Comments

Use clear and descriptive JSDoc comments for all classes, methods, and functions to improve maintainability and understanding of the codebase.

Swagger API Documentation

Use @nestjs/swagger (or your framework's equivalent) to generate Swagger documentation.

Annotate all controllers, DTOs, and endpoints with appropriate decorators for automatic API documentation.

Validation

Use DTOs and class-based validation with class-validator and class-transformer.

Apply appropriate decorators (e.g., @IsString(), @IsUUID(), @IsOptional()) to validate and transform incoming requests.

Testing

Write unit tests using Jest.

Cover all:

Core business logic

Edge cases

Controller methods

Service methods

Error handling paths

Code Quality and Reusability

Follow SOLID principles (Single Responsibility, Open/Closed, etc.).

Break reusable logic into services, utils, or helpers to avoid code duplication.

Keep controller logic minimal; move business logic to services.

Error Handling

Use consistent error formats with meaningful messages and HTTP status codes.

Handle edge cases such as:

Camera already in use

Missing or invalid data


External service failures (e.g., S3, Ngrok, RaspberryPi)